    ingredients: ["1 whole breadfruit, ripe but firm", "2 tbsp butter", "Salt to taste", "Optional: garlic butter or seasoned oil for serving"],
    steps: ["Place the whole breadfruit directly on a gas flame or barbecue grill over high heat.", "Roast, turning with tongs every 10 minutes, until completely charred and blackened all over \u2014 about 45-60 minutes.", "The breadfruit should feel soft when pressed and the stem will come away easily.", "Allow to cool slightly. Peel and discard the charred skin.", "Remove the core. Cut flesh into thick slices or chunks.", "Top with butter and a little salt while still hot.", "Serve alongside saltfish buljol, tomato choka or any stew."],
    nutrition: {"calories": "220", "protein": "2g", "carbs": "48g", "fat": "4g"},
