    cookGradient: "linear-gradient(135deg,#5C3A00,#9B6A00)",
    description: "Chewy, sweet coconut candy studded with ginger \u2014 a beloved Jamaican street sweet sold at bus stops and markets. Just coconut, sugar, ginger and water, cooked until it sets into glossy, chewy drops. Simple magic.",
    ingredients: ["1 whole dry coconut, grated (or 300g desiccated coconut)", "1\u00bd cups brown sugar", "1 cup water", "2 tbsp fresh ginger, grated", "1 tsp vanilla essence", "Pinch of salt"],
    steps: ["Combine sugar, water and ginger in a heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil.", "Add coconut and stir well. Continue cooking on medium heat, stirring constantly.", "Cook until the mixture thickens and begins to pull away from the sides of the pan \u2014 about 15-20 minutes.", "Add vanilla and a pinch of salt. Stir.", "Drop heaped tablespoons onto greased baking paper.", "Allow to cool completely \u2014 they will firm up as they cool.", "Store in an airtight container. Best eaten within 3 days."],
